## `<file-level: constants>`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-paths-1 -->

### Purpose
Path-length and name-length constants, mirrored from POSIX limits.

### Postconditions
- `PATH_MAX == 4096` â€” total byte length of a path string (matches Linux `PATH_MAX`).
- `NAME_MAX == 255` â€” single-component byte length (matches Linux `NAME_MAX`).

### Implementation Notes

```python
PATH_MAX = 4096
NAME_MAX = 255
```

